lse, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 3, "created_at": "2021-03-29T17:16:43Z", "updated_at": "2021-04-07T07:08:21Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "We know that the execution platform can impact the results. ATM we leave no trace of it. I am aware that this is not a trivial problem. I am aware we have the container extension to address some aspects of this problem. I am also aware that one could include manually craft platform information in the output.\r\n\r\nHowever, even something as simple as the following would go along way when investigating retrospectively. And often it is the metadata that you did not think of capturing that is the one you most desire ;-)\r\n\r\n```\r\n>>> platform.platform()\r\n'Linux-5.10.0-3-amd64-x86_64-with-glibc2.31'\r\n>>> platform.version()\r\n'#1 SMP Debian 5.10.13-1 (2021-02-06)'\r\n```\r\n\r\n", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/5535/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/5535/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null}